  "texts": [
    "Model adaptivityUnder the assumption that the ISAC system is static, the AI model is often trained offline and deployed online to improve the stability of the training process and meet real-time requirements.",
    "Once the AI model is well trained, its weights remain unchanged during the inference stage, which can cause performance degradation in some highly dynamic scenarios.",
    "TL, online training, and meta-learning [277,278] are potential techniques to improve the adaptation of AI models to dynamic scenarios.",
    "As discussed in Subsection 4.6, TL can fine-tune the pre-trained AI model in the source domain using the new samples in the target domain, thereby improving the model's adaptivity.",
    "Online training, which allows the AI model to update its parameters according to the new samples, is expected to adapt to the time-varying environment [279]."
  ],
